	<ofx:title lang="en">Symbols and Meanings</ofx:title>
	
	<ofx:paragraph lang="en">
		Icons are used as an instrument for user interaction with the system.
		These symbols and their meaning will now be explained.
        For most of the icons, you can move your mouse over the icon and if you leave the
        mouse pointer for a second, information about the meaning of the icon will appear.
	</ofx:paragraph>
	
		
	<ofx:paragraph lang="en">
		Icons are part of the graphical user interface and users can activate them using a mouse.
           Their placement on the screen - also in relation to other icons - may provide the user with further information about their usage.
		Table <ofx:reference target="table.user.ui.icons"/> gives a general overview of the existing icons.
	</ofx:paragraph>
	
